If you are really as wise and mighty

7
00:01:45,530 --> 00:01:46,780
as Father said,

8
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:48,270
just show up.

9
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:49,860
I don't want to

10
00:01:49,890 --> 00:01:50,890
die young.

11
00:02:11,070 --> 00:02:12,310
His Majesty granted the marriage.

12
00:02:12,310 --> 00:02:13,880
This is the highest honor and favor.

13
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,840
Marquis of Jing'an's Mansion
and Prince of Dingbei's Mansion

14
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:16,829
are becoming a marriage alliance.

15
00:02:15,940 --> 00:02:20,510
[Marquis of Jing'an's Mansion]

16
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,350
Today is the wedding.

17
00:02:22,380 --> 00:02:23,740
It's full of joy.

18
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:24,850
Anyone who congratulates

19
00:02:24,850 --> 00:02:26,190
will be rewarded with money...

20
00:02:26,190 --> 00:02:28,190
-Congratulations.
-For good luck.

21
00:02:30,190 --> 00:02:31,050
Suxin.

22
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:32,780
My Lord.

23
00:02:34,180 --> 00:02:35,000
Is there any news

24
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,370
from His Highness?

25
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,450
Madam of Auspicious Fortune
has been waiting in the backyard

26
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:39,240
for quite some time.

27
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,450
If this continues,

28
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,930
I'm afraid we won't
be able to keep it a secret.

29
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,520
Even if we can't, we must.

30
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:49,450
Today's wedding must
proceed without any mishap.

31
00:02:49,450 --> 00:02:50,920
His Majesty personally
bestowed this marriage.

32
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:51,850
What kind of girl

33
00:02:51,850 --> 00:02:53,329
could be so fortunate?

34
00:02:53,410 --> 00:02:54,200
Indeed.

35
00:02:54,329 --> 00:02:55,520
I heard that on the day of the betrothal,

36
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,630
the Prince of Dingbei made a special effort

37
00:02:56,630 --> 00:02:57,680
to add many more gifts.

38
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,960
You should have seen

39
00:02:59,510 --> 00:03:00,830
the betrothal gifts.

40
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:02,890
The Prince of Dingbei's Mansion
is truly exceptional.

41
00:03:02,890 --> 00:03:04,360
It's different from

42
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:04,960
ordinary noble families.

43
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:05,760
Isn't it?

44
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:06,520
Ladies.

45
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,130
-Congratulations, My Lord.
-Please, stay your steps.

46
00:03:08,130 --> 00:03:09,050
Here's the situation.

47
00:03:09,050 --> 00:03:10,240
Tan caught a chill

48
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:11,700
before bed last night.

49
00:03:11,850 --> 00:03:12,920
She's not feeling well.

50
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:13,820
Early this morning,

51
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:15,130
she complained of a severe headache

52
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:16,590
and can't stand any noise.

53
00:03:17,079 --> 00:03:17,770
By the way,

54
00:03:18,130 --> 00:03:19,520
the ladies are all in the backyard.

55
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,520
Perhaps you could go there first

56
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,890
to have some tea and catch up.

57
00:03:21,890 --> 00:03:22,760
-That sounds good.
-Okay.

58
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:23,410
Quickly,

59
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:24,960
attend to the ladies properly.

60
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,490
Ladies, take care as you go.

61
00:03:30,370 --> 00:03:31,000
My Lord,

62
00:03:31,770 --> 00:03:34,030
Chancellor Su and his wife have arrived.

63
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:36,560
Guard the courtyard well.

64
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:37,620
No one is allowed to enter.

65
00:03:37,620 --> 00:03:38,350
Yes, My Lord.

66
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:41,400
[Spring Blossoms, Autumn Fruits]

67
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:48,720
[The Sun and Moon Rise Eternally]

68
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:45,740
Chancellor Su.

69
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,920
You've finally arrived.

70
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:49,800
Well,

71
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,920
as Tan's godparents,

72
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:53,780
you haven't been attentive enough.

73
00:03:53,780 --> 00:03:55,520
You've come quite late.

74
00:03:56,350 --> 00:03:57,780
When we arrive

75
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,500
isn't important.

76
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:01,110
Even the best godparents

77
00:04:01,260 --> 00:04:02,410
are still guests.

78
00:04:02,410 --> 00:04:03,130
No, no, no.

79
00:04:03,170 --> 00:04:04,410
If you say that,

80
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:05,540
I won't be happy.

81
00:04:06,330 --> 00:04:07,370
Think about all those years

82
00:04:07,370 --> 00:04:08,950
when I wasn't in the capital.

83
00:04:08,950 --> 00:04:11,000
You took care of Tan.

84
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,570
Though I often bicker with you,

85
00:04:13,730 --> 00:04:15,900
I remember your kindness

86
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,670
to Tan.

87
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,410
If you stopped bickering with me,

88
00:04:22,410 --> 00:04:24,210
that would truly be unsettling.

89
00:04:24,650 --> 00:04:25,900
Indeed.

90
00:04:25,930 --> 00:04:27,320
Alright, enough joking.

91
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,320
At our age,

92
00:04:28,340 --> 00:04:29,940
we should be more dignified.

93
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:32,930
I'll go check on Tan

94
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:34,250
and have a private chat with her.

95
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:34,730
Madam.

96
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,590
I have a gift for her as well.

97
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,770
Madam, here's the situation.

98
00:04:40,270 --> 00:04:42,030
Tan caught a chill

99
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:43,590
and is suffering from a severe headache.

100
00:04:43,590 --> 00:04:45,120
When I went to see her earlier,

101
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,170
I was turned away.

102
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:49,120
Perhaps we should wait a bit.

103
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,680
You'll naturally see her

104
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,409
during the bridal procession.

105
00:04:54,470 --> 00:04:55,930
Even though you're her biological father,

106
00:04:55,930 --> 00:04:57,010
you're still a man.

107
00:04:57,030 --> 00:04:58,490
Tan naturally wouldn't want to see you now.

108
00:04:58,490 --> 00:05:00,320
I've been like a mother to Tan for years.

109
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:02,050
She wouldn't mind such things.

110
00:05:02,130 --> 00:05:02,580
No.

111
00:05:03,010 --> 00:05:03,700
Madam...

112
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:05,410
[Spring Blossoms, Autumn Fruits]

113
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:04,920
You, you, you...

114
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:07,000
They will have a mother-daughter talk.

115
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,090
Why are you following them?

116
00:05:08,090 --> 00:05:09,090
On such a joyous day,

117
00:05:09,090 --> 00:05:10,480
why are you so anxious?

118
00:05:11,230 --> 00:05:13,230
Could there be something wrong?

119
00:05:14,420 --> 00:05:15,740
What could be wrong?

120
00:05:15,770 --> 00:05:16,770
Of course.

121
00:05:17,460 --> 00:05:20,300
I... I'm just excited.

122
00:05:20,210 --> 00:05:24,050
[The Sun and Moon Rise Eternally]

123
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:24,920
Marquis, Chancellor.

124
00:05:24,140 --> 00:05:29,010
[Spring Blossoms, Autumn Fruits]

125
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,090
-Welcome.
-Congratulations!

126
00:05:26,090 --> 00:05:27,120
Please, please, please.

127
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:27,800
Please.

128
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:29,580
Please.

129
00:05:31,530 --> 00:05:32,800
The joy of marrying off a daughter

130
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,530
is life's greatest happiness.

131
00:05:34,540 --> 00:05:35,780
Indeed.

132
00:05:36,170 --> 00:05:37,409
The greatest happiness.

133
00:05:37,409 --> 00:05:38,090
The greatest happiness.

134
00:05:38,090 --> 00:05:39,420
That's right.

135
00:05:56,270 --> 00:05:57,670
Greetings, Your Grace.

136
00:05:57,700 --> 00:05:58,840
I've come to see Tan

137
00:05:58,860 --> 00:06:00,630
and have a private chat with her.

138
00:06:00,630 --> 00:06:01,450
Please don't be offended, Your Grace.

139
00:06:01,450 --> 00:06:02,950
Her Ladyship has a headache today

140
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:04,530
and instructed early on not to see anyone.

141
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:05,680
Tan is ill?

142
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:07,610
That makes it even more important
for me to see her.

143
00:06:07,610 --> 00:06:08,320
Your Grace,

144
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,090
Her Ladyship is resting.

145
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:12,320
Perhaps you could go to the backyard first.

146
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:13,360
Once Her Ladyship is dressed,

147
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,730
it won't be too late to see her.

148
00:06:14,730 --> 00:06:15,770
What time is it now?

149
00:06:15,770 --> 00:06:17,210
Tan is still resting?

150
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:18,770
If she misses the auspicious time
for departure,

151
00:06:18,770 --> 00:06:19,880
it would be bad luck.

152
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:20,920
Yes, yes.

153
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,170
Please rest assured, Your Grace.

154
00:06:23,170 --> 00:06:24,410
Her Ladyship is aware

155
00:06:24,410 --> 00:06:26,000
and will not miss the auspicious time.

156
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Perhaps you could go to the backyard first

157
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,130
and rest for a while.

158
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,170
Tan must be

159
00:06:34,170 --> 00:06:35,730
feeling shy before the wedding...

160
00:06:35,730 --> 00:06:36,210
Your Grace.

161
00:06:36,210 --> 00:06:37,870
So she's pretending
to be ill to avoid people.

162
00:06:37,870 --> 00:06:38,640
Tan.

163
00:06:38,670 --> 00:06:39,430
Your Grace.

164
00:06:40,070 --> 00:06:40,870
Tan.

165
00:06:40,890 --> 00:06:41,690
Your Grace.

166
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,890
Please forgive me, My Lady.

167
00:06:46,970 --> 00:06:48,850
Her Grace insisted on seeing you,

168
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:50,210
and I couldn't stop her.

169
00:06:51,990 --> 00:06:54,200
Is it godmother?

170
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:55,010
Tan.

171
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:56,950
What happened to your voice?

172
00:06:57,770 --> 00:06:58,980
Is it a severe cough?

173
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:02,850
Come,

174
00:07:04,550 --> 00:07:05,750
let me take a look.

175
00:07:08,980 --> 00:07:10,110
Fourth Miss,

176
00:07:11,650 --> 00:07:12,910
the medicine is ready.

177
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:15,480
You should drink it while it's hot.

178
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:17,340
It'll help cure the cough faster.

179
00:07:20,550 --> 00:07:22,300
Greetings, Your Grace.

180
00:07:24,270 --> 00:07:25,770
Fourth Miss, be careful

181
00:07:25,790 --> 00:07:27,630
not to pull off the veil.

182
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,320
Earlier, during the face-painting,

183
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:31,480
Madam of Auspicious Fortune
repeatedly reminded us

184
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:32,610
that the veil

185
00:07:32,650 --> 00:07:34,409
must be removed by you

186
00:07:34,409 --> 00:07:35,970
after bidding farewell to your parents.

187
00:07:35,970 --> 00:07:38,700
Otherwise, it's considered
very inauspicious.

188
00:07:39,530 --> 00:07:40,290
Your Grace,

189
00:07:40,290 --> 00:07:41,680
wouldn't you agree?

190
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:44,120
Naturally.

191
00:07:45,050 --> 00:07:46,710
The custom of veiling the face

192
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:48,580
is meant to bring good luck.

193
00:07:52,730 --> 00:07:53,530
Tan,

194
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:56,210
this is a small token from me.

195
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:58,360
Come,

196
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,880
let me put it on for you.

197
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:18,480
The auspicious time is near.

198
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:20,950
You should prepare to depart.

199
00:08:21,090 --> 00:08:23,530
I'll go wait in the front hall.

200
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,410
Tan.

201
00:08:59,770 --> 00:09:00,490
Didn't we agree

202
00:09:00,490 --> 00:09:01,960
I'd see your makeup first?

203
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:02,560
Why did you already

204
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:03,490
cover your face with the bridal veil?

205
00:09:03,490 --> 00:09:04,360
Miss Minmin.

206
00:09:05,290 --> 00:09:05,750
This...

207
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,420
Lyu'e?

208
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:10,740
Miss...

209
00:09:11,410 --> 00:09:12,490
Miss Minmin.

210
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:12,990
What...

211
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,680
What's going on?

212
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:15,560
Where is Tan?

213
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,200
Thankfully, Madam of Auspicious Fortune
from the palace

214
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,920
has never seen Fourth Miss before,

215
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:24,580
Otherwise, this wouldn't
have held up till now.

216
00:09:25,380 --> 00:09:26,530
What exactly happened?

217
00:09:26,530 --> 00:09:27,460
Where did Tan go?

218
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,010
We don't know.

219
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:36,780
We can only keep it secret
for as long as we can.

220
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,600
What time is it?

221
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,410
My Lord.

222
00:10:01,410 --> 00:10:03,070
It's now the auspicious hour.

223
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,720
Wasn't it said that Prince of Rui

224
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,800
would come to escort the bride?

225
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,000
Why isn't he here yet?

226
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:11,050
Yeah.

227
00:10:11,370 --> 00:10:13,230
Could something have gone wrong?

228
00:10:20,770 --> 00:10:22,410
The auspicious hour has arrived.

229
00:10:22,410 --> 00:10:23,960
Why hasn't Tan come out yet

230
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,690
to bid farewell to her parents?

231
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,650
It's...

232
00:10:27,050 --> 00:10:28,720
Could it be that you're reluctant
to part with your daughter

233
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:30,250
and decided to hide her?

234
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:32,050
How could that be?

235
00:10:32,050 --> 00:10:32,960
Hard to say.

236
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:45,250
The auspicious hour is here.
Begin the bride's ritual.

237
00:10:45,650 --> 00:10:47,410
Great!

238
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,370
Chancellor Su, please.

239
00:10:54,050 --> 00:10:54,650
Alright.

240
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:04,440
Spring is the first of seasons,

241
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:07,440
and filial piety is the foremost of virtues.

242
00:11:08,130 --> 00:11:10,600
The precious daughter marries today,

243
00:11:11,290 --> 00:11:14,600
bidding farewell with tears to her parents.

244
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:34,890
Tan.

245
00:11:37,010 --> 00:11:38,220
Today you are getting married,

246
00:11:38,220 --> 00:11:40,620
As your father, my heart is full of comfort.

247
00:11:41,370 --> 00:11:42,800
In the days ahead, with the prince,

248
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,920
you must treat each other with respect,

249
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:46,650
support one another to old age,

250
00:11:46,890 --> 00:11:48,200
work as one in both

251
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,490
joy and hardship.

252
00:11:56,210 --> 00:11:57,070
That's enough,

253
00:11:58,010 --> 00:12:00,320
Don't delay the auspicious departure time.

254
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,370
Go quickly now.

255
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:07,490
Tan.

256
00:12:08,620 --> 00:12:09,560
Tan.

257
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:13,490
I find it hard to part with you.

258
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:15,370
After you enter
the Prince of Dingbei's Mansion,

259
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:17,570
do come back to visit our mansion often,

260
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:20,150
and spend time with me and your godfather.

261
00:12:20,210 --> 00:12:21,320
Hurry and go,

262
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:23,250
the auspicious time is almost over.

263
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:24,050
Tan,

264
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,680
we didn't even get to meet earlier

265
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,130
at Zhaoshui House.

266
00:12:27,530 --> 00:12:29,190
Now at your wedding farewell,

267
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,630
surely I

268
00:12:30,650 --> 00:12:32,700
should at least have a proper look at you?

269
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:34,610
One glance, and I'll be at ease.

270
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:37,940
No.

271
00:12:38,290 --> 00:12:39,080
How dare you!

272
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,720
Such behavior

273
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:43,070
shows no respect to your elders.

274
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:47,700
Minmin, don't be rude.

275
00:12:49,260 --> 00:12:50,990
Old man, you don't understand.

276
00:12:51,130 --> 00:12:52,770
If the bridal veil of a new bride

277
00:12:52,770 --> 00:12:54,350
is lifted by someone else,

278
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:57,120
it's considered unlucky for her marriage.

279
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,530
Isn't that right,
Madam of Auspicious Fortune?

280
00:12:59,530 --> 00:13:00,890
It is indeed.

281
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:04,410
Your Grace's action is rather improper.

282
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:09,720
My wife and I

283
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:11,410
have treated Tan as our own.

284
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:13,080
To take one last look as we send her off,

285
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:14,320
what's wrong with that?

286
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:16,170
